<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="305" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,761,1195,2083]" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,265,1195,1219]" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antennae brown. Antennomere II longer than III. Pronotum with smoky stripe reaching posterior margin. Thoracic and abdominal pleurites and sternites with black spots (
<figureCitation box="[218,300,1292,1315]" captionStart="Figs 3" captionStartId="4.[151,188,2038,2057]" captionTargetBox="[242,1332,205,1992]" captionTargetId="figure-13@4.[179,1408,189,1996]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 3A–F. Dorsal and ventral surface. A–B – Hypoxys favachae sp. nov.; C–D – Hypoxys gaucho sp. nov.; E–F – Hypoxys hyalinofasciatus sp. nov. Scale bars = 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177533" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177533/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). Anterior excavation of metasternal process harboring fourth and almost whole third rostral segment (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 13" captionStartId="17.[150,187,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[179,1414,196,1988]" captionTargetId="figure-16@17.[173,1415,189,2015]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figs 13A–E. Hypoxys gaucho sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177551/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Fig. 13E</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[213,375,1355,1379]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[505,637,1356,1379]" captionStart="Figs 13" captionStartId="17.[150,187,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[179,1414,196,1988]" captionTargetId="figure-16@17.[173,1415,189,2015]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figs 13A–E. Hypoxys gaucho sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177551/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Figs 13A–D</figureCitation>
). Posterolateral angles developed, bent inwards, acuminate (
<figureCitation box="[653,748,1388,1411]" captionStart="Figs 13" captionStartId="17.[150,187,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[179,1414,196,1988]" captionTargetId="figure-16@17.[173,1415,189,2015]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figs 13A–E. Hypoxys gaucho sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177551/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup large, concave, parallel to dorsal rim, and almost reaching posterolateral angle, ventral margin thick and carinate, inner part medially notched, inner dorsal angle produced in long digitiform process (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 13" captionStartId="17.[150,187,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[179,1414,196,1988]" captionTargetId="figure-16@17.[173,1415,189,2015]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figs 13A–E. Hypoxys gaucho sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177551/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Figs 13C,D</figureCitation>
). Paramere with two lobes; anterior lobe square, large, and directed to base of proctiger; lateral lobe rounded (
<figureCitation box="[158,284,1612,1635]" captionStart="Figs 13" captionStartId="17.[150,187,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[179,1414,196,1988]" captionTargetId="figure-16@17.[173,1415,189,2015]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figs 13A–E. Hypoxys gaucho sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177551/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Figs 13C,D</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with dense crown of long setae on lateral excavations; posterior face subpentagonal and short (
<figureCitation box="[158,282,1676,1699]" captionStart="Figs 13" captionStartId="17.[150,187,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[179,1414,196,1988]" captionTargetId="figure-16@17.[173,1415,189,2015]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figs 13A–E. Hypoxys gaucho sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177551/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Figs 13C,D</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim with expansions long, acuminate, ventrolateral side broadly excavated and medially furrowed, dorsal side with light brown spot; surpassing level of posterolateral angles (
<figureCitation box="[343,437,1772,1795]" captionStart="Figs 13" captionStartId="17.[150,187,2034,2053]" captionTargetBox="[179,1414,196,1988]" captionTargetId="figure-16@17.[173,1415,189,2015]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figs 13A–E. Hypoxys gaucho sp. nov. A–D – pygophore in dorsal, ventral, posterior and posterolateral view, respectively; E – metasternal process. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5177551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5177551/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Fig. 13B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[456,644,1771,1795]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Unknown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,342,1804,1827]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Measurements</emphasis>
(n = 1; mm). Total length 15.0; head length 1.6; head width 3.2; pronotum width 9.4; abdomen width 7.5; length of antennomeres: I – 0.8; II – 1.7; III – 1.1; IV: missing; V: missing; scutellum length 6.7; scutellum width 5.4; pronotum length 2.7.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,761,1195,2083]" lastBlockId="16.[828,1437,190,437]" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,404,1963,1987]" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
See differential diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="favachae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">H. favachae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[254,337,1996,2019]" pageId="16" pageNumber="305" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Additionally, 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[487,599,1996,2019]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gaucho" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[487,599,1996,2019]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">H. gaucho</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[605,687,1996,2019]" pageId="16" pageNumber="305" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
shares with 
<taxonomicName authority="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes, 2021" authorityName="Mendonca &amp; Nunes &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2021" box="[209,377,2028,2051]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="305" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aspilogaster" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[209,377,2028,2051]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">H. aspilogaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[387,473,2028,2051]" pageId="16" pageNumber="305" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
the expansions of ventral rim long and narrow but both species can be separated by the shape of the superior process of genital cup and the posterior face of proctiger.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="305" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[828,1437,190,437]" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[828,956,254,278]" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after the people born in 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Rio Grande do Sul State</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[966,1035,286,309]" name="Brazil" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The name Gaucho is also used for the “cowboys” that traditionally inhabit the prairies (Pampa Biome) in 
<collectingCountry box="[944,1009,350,373]" name="Brazil" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1025,1233,350,373]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[1253,1346,350,373]" name="Uruguay" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry name="Argentina" pageId="16" pageNumber="305">Argentina</collectingCountry>
. Noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
